{"_id":"6HXNxcK0Q0jIkJHv","name":"1C. The Ambush on foot","content":"<p>As you struggle to hang on to the humvee, the sounds of artillery blasts and explosions muting into the background, you can't help but wonder what went wrong. Operation Reset felt like a modern D-day; you knew it would work because, at critical times, the US military has always come through with a victory until now. Glancing at the others in your unit that are also hanging on for dear life, you sense they are going through the same emotional battle.</p>\n<p>The road you are traveling is rough; a huge divot breaks you out of your daydream; you refocus your attention on maintaining your grasp of the rollbar. As the vehicle crests a small hill, you see a burning M113 APC about 100 meters down the road.</p>\n<p>Suddenly, the sound of a short-range missile catches your attention. Unlike the blasts you have heard while riding the humvee, this one is not off in the distance, but indicates incoming fire.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<section class=\"secret\" style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-5);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-5)\">\n<p>Helpers:</p>\n<p>@Actor[sCFb7QYEK2RwN30l]{Soviet Grenadier}</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[yOx9uc5dmjb8g8W6]{Explosions}</p>\n<p>@Actor[TriLLe1lBqUcK2nW]{GM Helper}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<span style=\"text-align:center\">@JournalEntry[rScVqdQScVLkPVtf]{⮜ Previous: 1A. Fleeing Kalisz} | @JournalEntry[HlghGVz6fGVgBCQw]{Next: 1D. After the Ambush⮞}</span></section>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xrutfo08ZKgCmTKc":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.6HXNxcK0Q0jIkJHv","hash":"5422dcea7a5c617d182a4f243edf2d69a59d34db"},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6c7356gjt","path":"Escape from Kalisz#/CF_SEP/1. Day One","color":"#000000"}}}
