{"_id":"rScVqdQScVLkPVtf","name":"1A. Fleeing Kalisz","content":"<p>In the immediate aftermath of the failed Operation Reset, you find yourself fleeing the failed operation in Kalisz. You and several comrades from the US 5th Mechanized Infantry Division are dodging incoming artillery fire, darting between sheltered positions, amongst the fleeing masses.</p>\n<p>As the adrenaline rush starts to subside, exhaustion begins to creep through your mind and body. You must find a safe place to rest and ride out the barrage. Seemingly in answer to your prayers, you see an M1114 HMMWV approaching and heading down the same road you are following. The vehicle slows as it gets close to you and someone from inside yells out:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"Hop on, we will get you out of here.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>If the party members get on the humvee it will proceed to the journal entry 1B. The Ambush. Otherwise, you can have them arrive on foot at the same location shortly after the attack has occurred in 1C. The Ambush on foot.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">@JournalEntry[pAhsCCP4kORBMz9i]{⮜ Previous: 0. You're On Your Own} | @JournalEntry[qFEYEVXDf5WILrIi]{Next: 1B. The Ambush ⮞} | @JournalEntry[6HXNxcK0Q0jIkJHv]{Next: 1C. The Ambush on foot ⮞}</p>\n</section>\n<p> </p>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"xrutfo08ZKgCmTKc":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.rScVqdQScVLkPVtf","hash":"230b25492e6db2745fcf9810cc1cc010ffef6244"},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6c7356gjt","path":"Escape from Kalisz#/CF_SEP/1. Day One","color":"#000000"}}}
